text.tspan: Episodes 1 & 2 make for the story's exposition, in which the two sisters are together, and
Powder mentions are at the high range at 9 and 8 count, respectively. Powder mentions count
then drops by 60% to just 3 in the Base Violence Necessary for Change; that is when Vi leaves
Powder to rescue Vander and later upon calling her Jinx. Vi gets imprisoned after and only gets
reunited with Jinx in episode 6, where we see a spike in Powder mentions again. The spike and
reunion end shortly after as the firelights take Vi in and then get set into talking the council
into taking Silco down. Finally, Powder mentions spike once again when she
kidnaps Vi in the finale.

text.data-name: Powder mentions spikes when she's with Vi, at an average of 8.6 an episode, compared to just 2.4 when the sisters are separated and flat up zero in Happy Progress Day, where Vi doesn't make an appearance.
